.TH getpw 3
.SH NAME
\*Lgetpw\*O \- get name from uid
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.nL
\*Lgetpw (
.nL
 uid_t \*Vuid\*L,
.nL
 char *\*Vbuf\*L ); \*O
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "getpw subroutine"
.iX "getpw subroutine" "getpwuid subroutine"
.iX "password file (general)" "getting name from"
The \*Lgetpw\*O routine has been superseded by \*Lgetpwuid\*O.
See \*Lgetpwent\*O(3).
.PP
The \*Lgetpw\*O
routine searches the password file for
the (numerical) \*Vuid\*O, and fills in \*Vbuf\*O
with the corresponding line;
it returns nonzero if \*Vuid\*O
could not be found.
The line is null terminated.
.SH ERRORS
.PP
Nonzero return on error.
.SH FILES
.PP
\*L/etc/passwd\*O
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.PP
\*Lgetpwent\*O(3), \*Lpasswd\*O(4)
